{"id": "4885f41bf4d8508fa7a66128fae8450fe187b1426ee6d04bbfa9a22aee29bbd0", "item_id": "21260b17fd:0", "text": "PxrBump used to provide the secondary bump on displaced tiles."}
{"id": "0f1226fba6761d0f52f2dfd63177b9a9c4f0be0b27588aadb276035d48382dbb", "item_id": "21260b17fd:1", "text": "Bump mapping is an inexpensive way to apply details to an object without modeling it or using displacement to change its shape. This is a shading \"trick\" where a supplied pattern can give the illusion of details."}
{"id": "4aa9766177c4d041b5a7d60b5c16e87d3fdf37472d2fdd38b1730f8db933914d", "item_id": "21260b17fd:2", "text": "This produces a bumped normal from a bump map (a scalar displacement map, so only the first channel is used for the displacement). Bumps are applied in"}
{"id": "2958d416d08aa5a472d7b509036cb7eafd542add84527e66a145ea64cb4cdc75", "item_id": "21260b17fd:5", "text": "object"}
{"id": "943a088c84570038282ed9b1bf7b4b6e676b078cb7beac2a172bb6a5fe4a098c", "item_id": "21260b17fd:4", "text": "space. The change in scale between"}
{"id": "a529e750ae959a78c356863f3fc843efd652fa76201d7cde719913ec2772f742", "item_id": "21260b17fd:6", "text": "space and"}
{"id": "97b0560280ed60a5a1eaa1bc45492543c8a986ad5a25b468c427eb83c3e88191", "item_id": "21260b17fd:7", "text": "current"}
{"id": "193cd20006314b60cf5c5bda5f238badd41dddedef39d811da49ca5b1929bee2", "item_id": "21260b17fd:8", "text": "space is automatically applied by the node."}
{"id": "d18c93a3074023c66aa3693f2e92aa9faa1fe89bb7f9ac66f01ea9464b2f7e16", "item_id": "21260b17fd:9", "text": "Texture atlas format files can be read in either UDIM (Mari) format or Mudbox format. This plugin also supports Rtx procedural texture plugins."}
{"id": "f102986b39effb31080ae442f61febe7ed58df1515c0711ccfadfe0311ccec81", "item_id": "21260b17fd:11", "text": "Scale"}
{"id": "4e65dc7240a3b37f7ed47c1435da897d0654422fa645935ea782c750ff676d12", "item_id": "21260b17fd:12", "text": "An object-space scale applied to the bump."}
{"id": "75081b593d15cf6e631971bc6768723f593b88b172477e40ae7d363e4829816d", "item_id": "21260b17fd:13", "text": "Disabled"}
{"id": "f11b9f862f87d94d73949f877ff77510be0bd86b23d7caf2f482f70d603faf85", "item_id": "21260b17fd:14", "text": "Turn off the bump effect, useful for debugging. Uses the geometric normal instead."}
{"id": "751a77bbfa814e41098c09534ea937b1230c81bec91f85f05b11df1fb48c2bf0", "item_id": "21260b17fd:42", "text": "Input Bump"}
{"id": "1e3abf61a37e3cad36b11b459b1cc39e76feb6a0c369fe5270957468288dcc5c", "item_id": "21260b17fd:37", "text": "If"}
{"id": "f68cea4e7febadd22efe7dfea0ef7f97ba2a8de79497735cf643728464a1f54e", "item_id": "21260b17fd:18", "text": "is connected (and"}
{"id": "971b974235a86ca628dcc713d6e2e8d975206cc84c858720ce046c2dab72855a", "item_id": "21260b17fd:38", "text": "Filename"}
{"id": "20865cfb1f320bb78b17c742d51088fa4ac650c074801eb19289e9601a1250a4", "item_id": "21260b17fd:20", "text": "is not specified), the pattern executes the upstream pattern netowrk connected to"}
{"id": "78d0cbb65c77d9649c52971c10378eee570b0a8a8edfabf464b7e4ab325a6ab6", "item_id": "21260b17fd:22", "text": "three times, once at the shading point and once at"}
{"id": "be7097dd342a707d764703fde533585395209875012be46f7488448dcf830f8d", "item_id": "21260b17fd:24", "text": ". Then it crosses the results to get the bump normal."}
{"id": "f32d5f3a439d6eff528cf140a07f8cbc73eab4e0faeb8008c0b27a34955a0ab3", "item_id": "21260b17fd:25", "text": "Note that if you have a fixed texture and UV, it is highly recommended to use the"}
{"id": "28d00ef2a9bc8ea2ccb59bed6687bdf10b1e18e51a5c0fd46f13e024ac268c81", "item_id": "21260b17fd:27", "text": "parameter below because it is 3 times faster!"}
{"id": "819cfcd771ec8fd7a65d04e6ca0a7393e37890b3a73cada06062cc606382fbd3", "item_id": "21260b17fd:30", "text": "is specified,"}
{"id": "3c63ef04ef415e76c8179e87c2dc2c3491a0c058b2681c4cf5a357466b948f81", "item_id": "21260b17fd:32", "text": "is ignored."}
{"id": "7985094bf7e918f028575a78dee8f885794f240560f112bf0d1d2c58dc9821e2", "item_id": "21260b17fd:34", "text": "The filename of the texture. If not provided,"}
{"id": "75226eacc808872575ff917a7bb831e9db8e91560c5883437b1ea3c4e5b6f2e8", "item_id": "21260b17fd:36", "text": "is used instead."}
{"id": "d211cfbcc26a39b757ccaff54a67711fea8441aa5ab674be736e9485327ca039", "item_id": "21260b17fd:39", "text": "is specified, the pattern has no upstream graph connected. Instead it reads the bump value from the texture file. The input file can be a color or monochrome file; if the file is RGB, only a single channel (as specified by the"}
{"id": "f006aa17de7681cdae37fe9fccbdbb515dbb50f4b25cb2828479c84f9e96b858", "item_id": "21260b17fd:40", "text": "First Channel Offset"}
{"id": "ab421bce86230ccc45ee6ec322f868cd8e88b76f336209f97c8478cf7ae09259", "item_id": "21260b17fd:41", "text": "parameter) is read. The bump pattern gets the derivatives from the texture at the same time it filters it, which provides a performance benefit over using"}
{"id": "fae969a59a309e426969b82a85bd7fb57223b23ea08f6b629906bd6df60d9b4a", "item_id": "21260b17fd:44", "text": "The PxrBump pattern currently does not allow modifying the manifold of the texture, use the below control."}
{"id": "009c03cc4a76f837307874312d0caf4244cd5841133073ccea9f346d65a24048", "item_id": "21260b17fd:45", "text": "Bump Manifold"}
{"id": "fd531854a20458bf6bb4d65b386549690a265ba041cc17d1595a6b73c77a77c5", "item_id": "21260b17fd:46", "text": "This takes an incoming connection of the"}
{"id": "b3180962910756fecdd99d178810e38530214de4f79f35c6beb26011807ccf91", "item_id": "21260b17fd:47", "text": "PxrBumpManifold2D"}
{"id": "dfa8ca3dda7768e23742a8c2ebe2d8c77c7b2ec4ec5e1f97af06df2c120ff0e6", "item_id": "21260b17fd:48", "text": "Advanced Texture Settings"}
{"id": "8fe14ecc5c2072813ce479fe2eabe100fbb085e782d1ec00a94bc2ef73d0ca8c", "item_id": "21260b17fd:49", "text": "MIPBias"}
{"id": "ef1ae501cd0e4bef78368c4a97815d65fe62b9950f31f2d4957c2516f2bfea17", "item_id": "21260b17fd:50", "text": "Bias MIP selection chosen for rendering to either a higher (negative integers) or lower resolution (positive integers) selection."}
{"id": "6960e01a00d0599446e00ff16d67c2dda5a8214709238c5b736828bf9540edca", "item_id": "21260b17fd:51", "text": "MaxResolution"}
{"id": "dd4d9465ab285286fc6fc2dfee9389ce2530e0a69862db3d7484f1cb664f31db", "item_id": "21260b17fd:52", "text": "Clamp MIP selection to a preferred maximum level. This may prevent the highest resolutions from being rendered depending on your selection."}
{"id": "9f088dbebd6c3c70a5ddbc2c943b11e4ca9acea5757b0b4f2b32479f0dbb747e", "item_id": "21260b17fd:53", "text": "Advanced"}
{"id": "5623398d54781bd64929648b12ce690f0a248c8cba6dcd57b88c37559630b38f", "item_id": "21260b17fd:54", "text": "Input Normal"}
{"id": "1e81d82861e7a023ad3097014e9eaf663e6839437a61673ef6b18ad739cd127d", "item_id": "21260b17fd:55", "text": "An additional normal to be added to the bump normal."}
{"id": "5b70861ec6dc456b6edc9821e99435f681a499beee808964c4ae46812225797e", "item_id": "21260b17fd:56", "text": "Reverse Normal"}
{"id": "820b7d76dc6d2569909ef574f2098fa98d0d55065a74c02dd3291847540e2f49", "item_id": "21260b17fd:57", "text": "Reverse the resulting normal."}
{"id": "22e51f047f90beac7936ab4aca9ca2269e04e5ca5be52b8d38f9abf5a0c348d3", "item_id": "21260b17fd:58", "text": "Adjust Amount"}
{"id": "f4e9ab18ac9e88ca25ff42b152b8676cb8aaa40ff823355e7fee1f3317bef874", "item_id": "21260b17fd:59", "text": "Amount to adjust the normals when the geometric normals are facing away from the camera. This is useful when we see cracks in the normals. You can find an example"}
{"id": "18ee1ea9b251b0a841885c123ba86d48505ac30953edd385a239068d48aa9faa", "item_id": "21260b17fd:62", "text": "Surface Normal Mix"}
{"id": "6f5e90f8ce996a9c442a916227414b1aa03a6755c52b0d7d9751c8e8f1c8ba90", "item_id": "21260b17fd:63", "text": "The amount to mix the resulting normals with the original surface normals. Toward 1.0 will mix in more surface normals. You can find an example"}
{"id": "8b76e2df9050f924b018cff8809cbc580f39a71664984ae54adf99defe9eaa2e", "item_id": "21260b17fd:66", "text": "Output Parameters"}
{"id": "7f69e5947418b1555a1d48ccadf50f5f065a7b50d03def2e60f0470abde48413", "item_id": "21260b17fd:67", "text": "resultN"}
{"id": "a0cff1de29adcb01a849ee0489d4d936508f384a733425f52237b4f28e65fdcb", "item_id": "21260b17fd:68", "text": "The bumped normal."}
